> > Of course if a polynomial time algorithm is discovered, all bets are
> > off, regardless of your key length!
> Very true.

No, it's not true. Say someone discovers how to factor d-digit numbers
in 2^50 d^11 machine operations. Will this affect the security of RSA?
Of course not. The equivalence ``polynomial-time <=> fast'' is not true
in either direction.

---Dan
